table.body:
The other person must respond to your nullity petition within 8 days, saying if they agree the marriage should be annulled.

If they agree, you can apply for a 'decree nisi'.

To get a decree nisi, fill in the [application for decree nisi/conditional order.](http://hmctsformfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=154 "application for decree nisi/conditional order"){:rel="external"}

##Statement in support of annulment

You must also fill in a statement confirming that what you said in your nullity petition is true.

Use one of the forms below, depending on whether your marriage is 'void' or 'voidable':

- [statement in support of annulment - void marriage](http://hmctsformfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2649 "statement in support of annulment - void marriage"){:rel="external"}
- [statement in support of annulment - voidable marriage](http://hmctsformfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2650 "statement in support of annulment - voidable marriage"){:rel="external"}

^See [when you can annul a marriage](/how-to-annul-marriage/when-you-can-annul-a-marriage "when you can annul a marriage") for the difference between 'void' and 'voidable' marriages.^
